</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uauffkee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Auff Kee</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/22/01 8:46:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ualr.edu/~jmglidden/auffside1.jpg height=148 width=114></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which race for a PvP necro?</span><hr size=1> Bards are hard as hell to kill in PvP, because they can pump their resists to insane levels, run faster than anything, shadowstep, cast while running, cancel anything you do manage to land on em, cancel any buffs you may have, poof pets in an instant, and charm every mob in the zone one by one till you're tired of trying.  But bards at any level have a hard time producing much damage in a PvP environment.  Put a well played bard in a group of PvPers and it's a totally different story.<br>
<br>
IMHO, necros have been nerfed way too much to be a formidable force in PvP.  Too many of their critical spells check MR.<br>
<br>
As for shammies, I've never played one, but I know that they can tank at least as well as a bard when they need to.  Most shammies I know have AC and hps that make me wanna cry.<br>
<br>
-Auff, 51 Bard of Epiphany <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urosilovechild.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RosiLovechild</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/23/01 2:35:03 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/image/21/2383421.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which race for a PvP necro?</span><hr size=1> Ok I play on Vallon Zek and here's my experience:<br>
<br>
Iksar necros own.  They really, really do.  And there aren't that many of them, plus you get to be on the dark team (Which is a better team imo).  On Vallon I know human necros are underplayed, so that might be the way you would want to go.<br>
<br>
Bards are practically unkillable.  Now that they've allowed root to override selos, it's getting more even.<br>
<br>
Wizards are one of the best pvp classes in the game--they have a wide variety of nukes (fire, cold, magic, etc) which makes it easier to find someone who has bad resist gear in at least one of those areas.  And nothing drops a warrior faster than a few ice comets.  <p><img src="http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/32/1793032.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=497.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=531.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.threadControl?topicID=530.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=530.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=530.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value